commit 21fde40d203f48b638e277d437859149314f5974
Author: Thierry Lepley <tlepley@cadence.com>
Date:   Mon May 9 13:25:59 2022 -0700

    Add the possibility to have variable size outputs (#5823)

    Summary:
    Add the possibility to specify a node with a variable number of outputs (we already had this feature for inputs but not for outputs)

    ### Documentation:
    This feature is useful in some cases we have encountered.

    The most visible change relates to the node API change : Node::getOutputName() now returns a std::string instead of a llvm::StringRef. This gives the freedom to generate output names on the fly and makes the output API consistent with the input API (that already returns  std::string for the same reason).

    Example:
    _BB.newBackendSpecificNode("TestNodeVector")
        .addMember(MemberType::VectorNodeValue, "Inputs")
        .addVariableResult("Outputs")
        .setDocstring("Node with variable number of inputs and outputs,")_;

    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/glow/pull/5823

    Test Plan: This is tested internally since we use this feature. I didn't add a unit test in this PR because this would mean adding a fake node to Glow just for testing purpose. Another solution is to create a backend just for testing this, what seems overkill.

