Author: Kyle Lee <kyleylee@fb.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 11 13:48:44 2022 -0700

    Refactor SLSBench/EBBench for common code

    Summary:
    Merge common code/logic from SLSBench and EBBench.  This is all now pushed within `CommonSLSEB.h`, where the enum type `BenchmarkType` will be used to branch among different functions.

    Note 1: Offset variable masking and related code in SLSBench in the `runSLS` function is not implemented, since it requires additional branches and a few explicit types being declared (added code complexity).  If this is performant critical, additional changes might be needed here.

    Note 2: An alternative to the above is to have a parent class (e.g. SLSBench) with EBBench inheriting most functions, but that will still require additional code sharing since `main` and `parseArg` are still part of the superclass.  This is not done here.

    Reviewed By: caogao

