    Convert DOT file to other formats using dot utility (#5765)

    Summary:
    **Summary**
    - Most of the times the target format of the command *-dump-graph-DAG" is other than the native DOT format.
    - For example in our case we convert the resulting DOT file to PDF format using the available dot utility from Linux like this:
      ```
      model-compiler ... -dump-graph-DAG=graph.dot
      dot -Tpdf graph.dot -o graph.pdf
      ```
    - With this code addition a user wanting directly a PDF format will use the command like this:
      ```
      model-compiler ... -dump-graph-DAG=graph.pdf
      ```
    - Behind the scenes the extension of the name will be used to infer the target format. If the target format is supported by the dot utility this conversion will be made using a system command.
    - Print the activations memory allocation efficiency in the bundle header file.

    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/glow/pull/5765

    Reviewed By: jfix71

    Differential Revision: D30545535

